    <p>Acca Ethics Film Fes­ti­val</p>
    <p>This year’s Acca (As­so­ci­a­tion of Chartered Cer­ti­fied Ac­coun­tants) Ethics Film Fes­ti­val, whose theme is “Re­think­ing Busi­ness For A Sus­tain­able Fu­ture”, will be held vir­tu­ally for the first time. In­dus­try ex­perts and thought lead­ers from around the re­gion will dis­cuss ethics and in­clu­siv­ity for ac­coun­tants and fi­nance pro­fes­sion­als.</p>
    <p>The screen­ings will be hosted on Net­flix Watch Party and panel dis­cus­sions will be held on Zoom. WHEN: Till Wed</p>
    <p>ADMISSION: $15 (mem­bers, af­fil­i­ates, stu­dents and ap­proved em­ploy­ers), $25 (pub­lic)</p>
    <p>INFO: ethics­film­fes­ti­val.com</p>
    <p>Fes­ti­val For Good</p>
    <p>Or­gan­ised by the Sin­ga­pore Cen­tre for So­cial En­ter­prise, this vir­tual fes­ti­val show­cases qual­ity prod­ucts and ser­vices by lo­cal and re­gional so­cial en­ter­prises. Par­tic­i­pants can reg­is­ter in ad­vance to join work­shops on top­ics such as cof­fee mixol­ogy and flower preser­va­tion, and soap-re­cy­cling ac­tiv­i­ties for chil­dren. WHEN: To­mor­row - Nov 22 ADMISSION: From $15</p>
    <p>INFO: fes­ti­val­for­good.sg</p>


